<sect1>
list_entry &lsqb;include/linux/list.h&rsqb;
<p>
Definition:

</p>

<p>
<verb>
&num;define list_entry(ptr, type, member) &bsol;
((type *)((char *)(ptr)-(unsigned long)(&amp;((type *)0)-&gt;member)))

</verb>
</p><p>
Meaning:

</p>
<p>
"list_entry" macro is used to retrieve a parent struct pointer,
 by using only one of internal struct pointer. 

</p>
